<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Tax Lien Code — MNTN CTV Funnel (per event)</title>
<style>
  :root{
    --ink:#1d2433; --muted:#5b6577; --line:#d8dee9; --paper:#ffffff;
    --ctv:#6d4ad6; --ctv-bg:#efeafb;
    --pool:#e8a33d; --pool-bg:#fdf3e3;
    --rtg:#e2603b; --rtg-bg:#fbeae4;
    --postreg:#3b6fb6; --postreg-bg:#e9f0fa;
    --launch:#2f9e57; --launch-bg:#e7f5ec;
    --rule:#1f9d8f; --rule-bg:#e8f6f4;
    --seqA:#1f9d8f; --seqB:#2bb6a3; --seqC:#3b6fb6; --seqD:#c0399c;
    --chip:#f1f4f9;
  }
  *{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
  body{font-family:-apple-system,"Segoe UI",Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;background:#eef1f5;color:var(--ink);padding:32px;line-height:1.4}
  .sheet{max-width:1180px;margin:0 auto;background:var(--paper);border-radius:14px;box-shadow:0 8px 30px rgba(20,30,50,.10);padding:34px 40px 44px;border-top:7px solid var(--ctv)}
  h1{font-size:23px;letter-spacing:-.2px}
  .sub{color:var(--muted);font-size:13.5px;margin-top:5px}

  .budget{display:flex;gap:14px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin:22px 0 6px}
  .bcard{flex:1;min-width:150px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:10px;padding:13px 15px;background:#fafbfd}
  .bcard .lab{font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.6px;color:var(--muted);font-weight:700}
  .bcard .val{font-size:20px;font-weight:800;margin-top:4px}
  .bcard .note{font-size:11.5px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:3px}
  .bcard.total{background:var(--ink);border-color:var(--ink)}
  .bcard.total .lab{color:#aeb7c7}
  .bcard.total .val{color:#fff}
  .bcard.total .note{color:#9fb0c9}
  .bcard.mntn{border-color:var(--ctv);background:var(--ctv-bg)}

  .rulebar{margin:18px 0 4px;border:2px solid var(--rule);background:var(--rule-bg);border-radius:12px;padding:13px 18px}
  .rulebar.attr{border-color:var(--ctv);background:var(--ctv-bg)}
  .rulebar .rt{font-weight:800;font-size:13px;color:#16776c;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:7px}
  .rulebar.attr .rt{color:#5a36b8}
  .rulebar .rs{font-size:12.5px;margin-top:4px;color:var(--ink)}

  .seqstrip{margin:22px 0 4px}
  .seqstrip .lab{font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.6px;color:var(--muted);font-weight:700;margin-bottom:8px}
  .seqrow{display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:stretch;flex-wrap:wrap}
  .seqcard{flex:1;min-width:150px;border-radius:10px;padding:11px 13px;color:#fff}
  .seqcard .g{font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;opacity:.9;letter-spacing:.4px}
  .seqcard .t{font-size:14px;font-weight:800;margin-top:1px}
  .seqcard .c{font-size:11.5px;margin-top:5px;opacity:.96}
  .seqarrow{align-self:center;color:var(--muted);font-weight:800;font-size:16px}

  .funnel{margin-top:24px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0}
  .arrow{width:0;height:0;border-left:13px solid transparent;border-right:13px solid transparent;border-top:15px solid var(--line);margin:11px 0}
  .arrow.flow{border-top-color:var(--pool)}

  .stage{width:100%;border:2px solid;border-radius:13px;padding:0;overflow:hidden}
  .stage-head{padding:11px 18px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;color:#fff;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap}
  .stage-head .title{font-size:15px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.2px}
  .stage-head .meta{font-size:12px;font-weight:600;opacity:.95}
  .pill{font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.3px;padding:3px 9px;border-radius:20px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.22);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.5)}
  .stage-body{padding:16px 18px;background:#fff}

  .lane{display:flex;gap:14px;flex-wrap:wrap}
  .adset{flex:1;min-width:300px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:10px;padding:13px 14px;background:#fcfdfe}
  .adset h4{font-size:13px;margin-bottom:8px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:7px;flex-wrap:wrap}
  .badge{font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;padding:2px 7px;border-radius:20px;color:#fff;letter-spacing:.3px}
  .row{font-size:12.5px;margin:5px 0;display:flex;gap:7px}
  .row .k{color:var(--muted);font-weight:700;min-width:84px;flex-shrink:0}
  .chips{display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap}
  .chip{background:var(--chip);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:7px;padding:3px 8px;font-size:11.5px;white-space:nowrap}
  .chip.aud{background:#eef6ff;border-color:#cfe2fa}
  .chip.cre{background:#f3eafb;border-color:#e2cdf5}
  .chip.warn{background:#fff3cd;border-color:#f3e0a3;color:#8a6d00;font-weight:700}
  .single{border:1px dashed var(--line);border-radius:10px;padding:12px 14px;background:#fcfdfe;font-size:12.5px}
  .stage-foot{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:12px;padding-top:10px;border-top:1px dashed var(--line)}
  .stage-foot b{color:var(--ink)}

  .launchbar{width:100%;background:var(--launch);color:#fff;border-radius:13px;padding:15px 18px;text-align:center}
  .launchbar .t{font-size:16px;font-weight:800}
  .launchbar .s{font-size:12.5px;opacity:.95;margin-top:3px}

  h2{font-size:16px;margin:34px 0 4px;letter-spacing:-.2px}
  .h2sub{font-size:12.5px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:12px}
  table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:12.5px}
  th,td{text-align:left;padding:9px 11px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
  th{background:#f6f8fb;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;color:var(--muted)}
  td b{color:var(--ink)}
  tr:last-child td{border-bottom:none}

  .legend{margin-top:28px;font-size:11.5px;color:var(--muted);border-top:1px solid var(--line);padding-top:14px}
  .legend b{color:var(--ink)}
  @media print{body{background:#fff;padding:0}.sheet{box-shadow:none;border-radius:0}}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="sheet">

  <h1>Tax Lien Code — MNTN CTV funnel (per event)</h1>
  <div class="sub">Complete MNTN funnel as a 4th per-event channel, built on the platform's actual mechanics (Adam Walker / MNTN deck, June 11): household sequencing, MNTN Matched, identity graph and native attribution. All inside <b>$65K blended per event (Meta + Google + MNTN)</b>. Spend baselines: Google Ads 8019545382 and Meta, pull June 16, 2026.</div>

  <!-- BUDGET ENVELOPE -->
  <div class="budget">
    <div class="bcard">
      <div class="lab">Meta / event</div>
      <div class="val">~$50K</div>
      <div class="note">Trims ~$4K from baseline ($54K) — cuts the LAL PB 10% ad set</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bcard">
      <div class="lab">Google / event</div>
      <div class="val">~$8K</div>
      <div class="note">Event layer post-consolidation (was ~$18K un-consolidated)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bcard mntn">
      <div class="lab">MNTN / event</div>
      <div class="val">~$6.5K</div>
      <div class="note">CTV sequence $4K + RetargetView $1.5K + Post-reg $1K</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bcard total">
      <div class="lab">Blended / event</div>
      <div class="val">~$64.5K</div>
      <div class="note">No contracts, no setup fees · MNTN auto-optimizes to budget + goal</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- INSIGHT 1: FUNDING -->
  <div class="rulebar">
    <div class="rt">💡 MNTN is funded by the Google consolidation — not a Meta cut</div>
    <div class="rs">Meta (~$54K) + Google (~$18K) per event already totals <b>~$72K</b>, over the cap. Consolidating Google prospecting into one evergreen engine drops Google from ~$18K to ~$8K, <b>freeing ~$10K</b>. MNTN takes ~$6.5K and Meta only trims ~$4K. Without the Google consolidation, $65K doesn't fit.</div>
  </div>

  <!-- INSIGHT 2: ATTRIBUTION SOLVED -->
  <div class="rulebar attr">
    <div class="rt">✅ The attribution problem (what the client pushed on) is solved in-platform</div>
    <div class="rs">What stalled the March test — "0 conversions, can't prove value" — is addressed by MNTN's native stack: <b>Verified Visits</b>, an <b>Incrementality + New-to-Brand</b> dashboard (proves net-new customers), drill-down to conversion-ID by campaign/creative/network/geo, and <b>Google Analytics + HubSpot</b> integration (first CTV platform with direct lead attribution). Answers the client's "which platform/campaign/ad drove the most qualified leads" directly.</div>
  </div>

  <!-- SEQUENCING STRIP -->
  <div class="seqstrip">
    <div class="lab">The spine: household sequencing (MNTN serves in order to the same home — 2X ROAS vs non-sequenced)</div>
    <div class="seqrow">
      <div class="seqcard" style="background:var(--seqA)"><div class="g">GROUP 1 · AWARENESS</div><div class="t">Who Brian is</div><div class="c">Direct Call Out · Aspirational Legacy</div></div>
      <div class="seqarrow">→</div>
      <div class="seqcard" style="background:var(--seqB)"><div class="g">GROUP 2 · CONSIDERATION</div><div class="t">Proof / credibility</div><div class="c">1-on-1 with Student · Walk and Talk</div></div>
      <div class="seqarrow">→</div>
      <div class="seqcard" style="background:var(--seqC)"><div class="g">GROUP 3 · INTENT</div><div class="t">Event urgency</div><div class="c">Seats Filling Fast · Event Dates</div></div>
      <div class="seqarrow">→</div>
      <div class="seqcard" style="background:var(--seqD)"><div class="g">GROUP 4 · CONVERT</div><div class="t">Registration CTA</div><div class="c">End card: logo + taxliencode.com + date</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="funnel">

    <!-- STAGE 1: SEQUENCED CTV -->
    <div class="stage" style="border-color:var(--ctv)">
      <div class="stage-head" style="background:var(--ctv)">
        <span class="title">1 · Sequenced CTV — reach &amp; build demand</span>
        <span class="meta">MNTN Performance TV · ~$4K/event · window E-21 → E-2 · Goal: Verified Visit / Lead</span>
        <span class="pill">GROUPS 1→4</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stage-body" style="background:var(--ctv-bg)">
        <div class="lane">
          <div class="adset">
            <h4><span class="badge" style="background:var(--ctv)">AUDIENCE</span> MNTN Matched + 3rd Party</h4>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">MNTN Matched</span><span class="chips"><span class="chip aud">AI keywords: tax lien / investing intent</span></span></div>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">3rd Party</span><span class="chips"><span class="chip aud">LiveRamp in-market: Financial / Investing</span></span></div>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Exclude (1P)</span><span class="chips"><span class="chip">Workshop Buyers (CRM upload)</span><span class="chip">Site converters</span></span></div>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Geo</span><span>Event city + DMA</span></div>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Why</span><span>MNTN Matched = 6x more site traffic and 2x higher ROAS than segment targeting</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="adset">
            <h4><span class="badge" style="background:var(--ctv)">CREATIVE · 16x9</span> 4 groups in sequence</h4>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Groups</span><span>Awareness → Consideration → Intent → Convert (above)</span></div>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Production</span><span class="chips"><span class="chip cre">QuickFrame AI generates/resizes 16x9</span></span></div>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Best practice</span><span>Persistent logo + URL + CTA + consistent VO = −41% CPV / +112% CR / +48% VR</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="stage-foot">CTV is not clickable — it works via <b>view-through</b>. The sequence prevents fatigue (sets in at 3.5X frequency) and moves the household through the narrative instead of repeating one ad. The Mar–Apr TLC test already showed traction: ~$5.8K over 11 days, 240K households, cost/visit down to $6.51.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arrow flow"></div>

    <!-- POOL -->
    <div class="stage" style="border-color:var(--pool)">
      <div class="stage-head" style="background:var(--pool)">
        <span class="title">⟳ CTV-exposed + visitor pool (Identity Graph)</span>
        <span class="meta">Cookieless · 99%+ of US homes · no spend</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stage-body" style="background:var(--pool-bg)">
        <div class="single">MNTN's Identity Graph (Device IDs, IPs, RampIDs, Google Analytics IDs) captures who was exposed to the TV ad and who visited the site without registering. It feeds RetargetView and measures deterministically across 400M+ devices.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arrow flow"></div>

    <!-- STAGE 2: RETARGETVIEW + 1P -->
    <div class="stage" style="border-color:var(--rtg)">
      <div class="stage-head" style="background:var(--rtg)">
        <span class="title">2 · RetargetView — convert the reached</span>
        <span class="meta">MNTN retargeting · ~$1.5K/event · window E-14 → E · Goal: Lead</span>
        <span class="pill">BOFU</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stage-body" style="background:var(--rtg-bg)">
        <div class="lane">
          <div class="adset">
            <h4><span class="badge" style="background:var(--rtg)">AUDIENCE</span> Exposed + visitors not registered</h4>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Include</span><span class="chips"><span class="chip aud">CTV-exposed + site visitors L21+</span></span></div>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Exclude (1P)</span><span class="chips"><span class="chip">Registrants (CRM)</span><span class="chip">Workshop Buyers</span></span></div>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Geo</span><span>Event city + radius</span></div>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Creative</span><span class="chips"><span class="chip cre">Group 3 (Urgency)</span><span class="chip cre">Group 4 (Convert)</span></span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="stage-foot">Closes the TV view-through loop with a bottom-funnel push to those exposed but not registered. This is the "engaged ≥21 days" layer you wanted — built via First Party + the pixel window.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arrow flow"></div>

    <!-- STAGE 3: POST-REG -->
    <div class="stage" style="border-color:var(--postreg)">
      <div class="stage-head" style="background:var(--postreg)">
        <span class="title">3 · Post-registration — warm &amp; lift show rate</span>
        <span class="meta">CTV + retargeting · ~$1K/event · window E-7 → event day</span>
        <span class="pill">SHOW RATE</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stage-body" style="background:var(--postreg-bg)">
        <div class="lane">
          <div class="adset">
            <h4><span class="badge" style="background:var(--postreg)">AUDIENCE · FIRST PARTY</span> Registered, not yet attended</h4>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Source</span><span class="chips"><span class="chip aud">Event registrant list (CRM upload / HubSpot)</span></span></div>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Creative</span><span class="chips"><span class="chip cre">Why Did You Come?</span><span class="chip cre">1-on-1 with Student</span><span class="chip cre">Walk and Talk</span></span></div>
            <div class="row"><span class="k">Goal</span><span>Social proof / belonging → raise attendance</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="stage-foot">Show rate is TLC's biggest lever. Warming the registrant in event week with testimonial attacks where the funnel loses the most value. Mirrors Meta's Lead Nurture — here in CTV.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="arrow flow"></div>

    <div class="launchbar">
      <div class="t">★ Event day — attendance</div>
      <div class="s">MNTN builds incremental demand at the top and protects show rate at the end — additive to the funnel, not cannibal. Incrementality is measured in the New-to-Brand dashboard.</div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- MEASUREMENT -->
  <h2>Measurement &amp; attribution — how we prove value to the client</h2>
  <div class="h2sub">The direct answer to what stalled in March. All native to MNTN, no reliance on manual UTMs.</div>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Layer</th><th>What it proves</th><th>How</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><b>Verified Visits</b></td><td>Incremental traffic the TV drove</td><td>Core metric + Visit Rate, drill to conversion-ID</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>Incrementality + New-to-Brand</b></td><td>Net-new customers above organic/other channels</td><td>Incrementality dashboard (lift vs control)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>HubSpot (direct lead)</b></td><td>Which lead/registration came from MNTN</td><td>Native integration — 1st CTV with direct lead attribution</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>Google Analytics</b></td><td>Cross-check against the client's trusted attribution</td><td>GA integration + breakouts by campaign/creative/network/geo</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <!-- INVENTORY -->
  <h2>MNTN inventory — product, window and budget</h2>
  <div class="h2sub">All geo-locked to the event city, on premium inventory (Hulu, HBO Max, Disney, Paramount — 150+ direct deals).</div>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Stage</th><th>MNTN product</th><th>Audience</th><th>Window</th><th>Budget/event</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><b>1 · Sequenced CTV</b></td><td>Performance TV (4 groups)</td><td>MNTN Matched + 3P · excl. WB/converters</td><td>E-21 → E-2</td><td>~$4,000</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>Pool</b></td><td>Identity Graph / pixel</td><td>Exposed + visitors</td><td>continuous</td><td>—</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>2 · RetargetView</b></td><td>Retargeting</td><td>Exposed + visitors L21+ not registered</td><td>E-14 → E</td><td>~$1,500</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>3 · Post-reg</b></td><td>Performance TV + retargeting</td><td>First Party: registered, not attended</td><td>E-7 → event day</td><td>~$1,000</td></tr>
      <tr><td colspan="4"><b>Total MNTN per event</b></td><td><b>~$6,500</b></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <!-- BUDGET FIT -->
  <h2>How it fits in $65K per event</h2>
  <div class="h2sub">The headroom doesn't come from Meta — it comes from consolidating Google prospecting.</div>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Channel</th><th>Today (no MNTN)</th><th>Proposed (with MNTN)</th><th>Move</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><b>Meta</b></td><td>~$54K</td><td>~$50K</td><td>Trim ~$4K (cut LAL PB 10%)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>Google</b></td><td>~$18K (2 TOFU DG + Search)</td><td>~$8K (event layer only)</td><td><b>Frees ~$10K via evergreen consolidation</b></td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>MNTN</b></td><td>$0 (or $10K/mo national)</td><td>~$6.5K per event</td><td>Fills the freed space</td></tr>
      <tr><td><b>Blended</b></td><td>~$72K (over cap)</td><td><b>~$64.5K</b></td><td>Fits $65K</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="legend">
    <b>The core move:</b> MNTN comes in as an incremental sequenced-TV layer funded by the Google consolidation — it doesn't pull weight from Meta. Without the consolidation, the $65K cap isn't reachable (real run-rate ~$72K).
    <br><b>Sequencing:</b> 4 groups served in order to the same household (Awareness → Consideration → Intent → Convert) = 2X ROAS vs non-sequenced; avoids the fatigue that sets in at 3.5X frequency.
    <br><b>Attribution:</b> Verified Visits + Incrementality/New-to-Brand + HubSpot (direct lead) + Google Analytics. Solves March's "0 conversions" and the client's ask to know what drives the most qualified leads.
    <br><b>Creative:</b> QuickFrame AI generates/resizes the 16x9 cuts (closes the in-stream gap) and publishes to MNTN/Meta/YouTube. End card always with logo + taxliencode.com + event date.
    <br><b>Open decisions:</b> does the $65K cap include MNTN's ~$5K/mo mgmt fee? · does per-event MNTN replace or add to the current $10K/mo national evergreen? · is the cap an OKR or the real history (live ~$72K)?
    <br><b>Sources:</b> "MNTN Performance TV x Single Grain" + "Creative Best Practices &amp; Sequencing" decks (Adam Walker, MNTN, June 11, 2026). Meta/Google per-event spend — live pull June 16, 2026, account 8019545382. MNTN test — brain.md + Slack #tax-lien-code.
  </div>

</div>
</body>
</html>
